10/09/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- The state department sent a letter to the US Congress on Tuesday (9 September) announcing that the administration has decided to provide up to $8.5 billion in loans to Turkey. The money will be disbursed over an 18-month period, starting as early as 20 September. According to the letter, the loan would be used to service Ankara's debts, particularly those to the United States and international financial institutions.
In other news, Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul predicted Tuesday that his country would become a full member of the EU in 2010. First however, Ankara must receive a date for starting accession negotiations. (Hurriyet, Milliyet - 10/09/03; Reuters, NTV, AFP - 09/09/03)
